results.name: a(n) = A080969(n)/A080967(A080979(A080970(n))).
comment: Donaghey shows in his paper that the orbit size (under the automorphism A057505/A057506) of each non-branch-reduced tree encoded by A080971(n) is divisible by the orbit size of the corresponding branch-reduced tree. This sequence gives the corresponding ratio.
reference: R. Donaghey, Automorphisms on Catalan trees and bracketing, J. Combin. Theory, Series B, 29 (1980), 75-90.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_ Mar 02 2003
